name: __make_cell
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: __register_test_classes
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: abs
summary: Absolute value or magnitude of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `y = abs(x)` returns the absolute value of real inputs and the magnitude (modulus) of complex inputs. For tensors, the operation is applied element-wise following MATLAB's broadcasting rules.

name: accept
summary: Accept a pending client connection on a TCP server.
description: `accept(server)` waits for a pending TCP connection on the socket created by `tcpserver`. When a client connects, the builtin returns a MATLAB-compatible struct that mirrors the `tcpclient` object.

name: acos
summary: Element-wise inverse cosine with MATLAB-compatible complex promotion.
description: `Y = acos(X)` computes the inverse cosine (in radians) of every element of `X`. Results match MATLAB semantics for real, logical, character, and complex inputs.

name: acosh
summary: Inverse hyperbolic cosine with MATLAB-compatible complex promotion.
description: `Y = acosh(X)` evaluates the inverse hyperbolic cosine of each element in `X`.

name: addlistener
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: addpath
summary: Add folders to the MATLAB search path used by RunMat.
description: `addpath` prepends or appends folders to the MATLAB search path that RunMat consults when resolving functions, scripts, classes, and data files.

name: all
summary: Check whether every element of an array slice is nonzero with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `all(X)` returns logical `true` when every element of the requested slice of `X` is nonzero. When you omit the dimension, the reduction runs along the first non-singleton axis, mirroring MATLAB.

name: and
summary: Element-wise logical AND for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values.
description: `and(A, B)` returns the element-wise logical AND of its inputs. Any non-zero value (including `NaN`) evaluates to `true`.

name: angle
summary: Phase angle of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `angle(x)` returns the phase angle (argument) of each element in `x`. The values are reported in radians and match MATLAB semantics exactly.

name: any
summary: Test whether any element of an array is nonzero with MATLAB-compatible options.
description: `any(X)` returns logical `true` wherever at least one element of the requested slice of `X` is nonzero.

name: argsort
summary: Return the permutation indices that would sort tensors along a dimension.
description: `argsort(X)` returns the permutation indices that order `X` the same way `sort(X)` would.

name: arrayfun
summary: Apply a function element-wise to array inputs.
description: `arrayfun(func, A1, A2, â¦)` evaluates `func` for every element (or element-wise combination) of the supplied arrays.

name: asin
summary: Element-wise inverse sine with MATLAB-compatible complex promotion.
description: `Y = asin(X)` computes the inverse sine (in radians) of every element of `X`. Results follow MATLAB semantics for real, logical, character, and complex inputs.

name: asinh
summary: Inverse hyperbolic sine of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `Y = asinh(X)` evaluates the inverse hyperbolic sine of every element in `X`.

name: assert
summary: Throw a MATLAB-style error when a logical or numeric condition evaluates to false.
description: `assert(cond, ...)` aborts execution with a MATLAB-compatible error when `cond` is false or contains any zero/NaN elements.

name: atan
summary: Arctangent of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `Y = atan(X)` computes the inverse tangent (in radians) of every element of `X`. The operation runs element-wise, supports real and complex numbers, and honors MATLAB's broadcasting semantics.

name: atan2
summary: Quadrant-aware inverse tangent atan2(y, x) with MATLAB-compatible broadcasting.
description: `theta = atan2(y, x)` computes the four-quadrant inverse tangent of the point `(x, y)`. It returns angles in radians covering the range `(-pi, pi]`, giving robust results even when `x` is zero.

name: atanh
summary: Inverse hyperbolic tangent with MATLAB-compatible complex promotion.
description: `Y = atanh(X)` evaluates the inverse hyperbolic tangent of every element in `X`.

name: bandwidth
summary: Compute the lower and upper bandwidth of a matrix.
description: `bandwidth(A)` inspects the nonzero pattern of a matrix and reports two numbers: the lower bandwidth (how many subdiagonals contain nonzeros) and the upper bandwidth (how many superdiagonals contain nonzeros).

name: bar
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: call_method
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: cat
summary: Concatenate arrays along a specified dimension while preserving MATLAB semantics.
description: `cat(dim, A1, A2, â¦)` concatenates arrays along the dimension `dim`, producing a new array whose slices along that dimension are the input arrays.

name: cd
summary: Change the current working folder or query the folder that RunMat is executing in.
description: `cd` displays the current working folder or switches RunMat to a different folder.

name: ceil
summary: Round values toward positive infinity.
description: `ceil(X)` rounds each element of `X` toward positive infinity, returning the smallest integer greater than or equal to the input.

name: cell
summary: Create empty MATLAB cell arrays.
description: `cell` constructs cell arraysâcontainers that can hold heterogeneous values in each element.

name: cell2mat
summary: Convert a cell array of numeric, logical, complex, or character blocks into a dense MATLAB array.
description: `cell2mat(C)` concatenates the numeric, logical, complex, or character arrays stored in the cell array `C` into a single dense MATLAB array.

name: cellfun
summary: Apply a function to the contents of each cell array element.
description: `cellfun` maps a function over one or more cell arrays.

name: cellstr
summary: Convert text to a cell array of character vectors.
description: `cellstr` converts character arrays, string arrays, or cell arrays of character vectors into a cell array whose elements are character vectors (1-by-N char arrays).

name: char
summary: Convert numeric codes, strings, and cell contents into a character array.
description: `char` converts its inputs into a character array.

name: chol
summary: Cholesky factorization with MATLAB-compatible upper and lower forms.
description: `chol(A)` computes a Cholesky factorization of a Hermitian positive-definite matrix `A`. By default, it returns the upper-triangular factor `R` satisfying `R' * R = A`.

name: Circle.area
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: circshift
summary: Rotate arrays circularly along one or more dimensions.
description: `circshift(A, K)` rotates the elements of `A` circularly. Positive shifts move elements toward higher indices, wrapping values that fall off the end back to the beginning.

name: class
summary: Return the MATLAB class name for scalars, arrays, and objects.
description: `class(x)` returns the name of the MATLAB class that `x` belongs to. The result is a string scalar that you can use for diagnostics, branching, or display logic.

name: classref
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: close
summary: Close TCP clients or servers created by tcpclient, tcpserver, or accept.
description: `close` releases TCP clients and servers that were created with `tcpclient`, `tcpserver`, or `accept`.

name: colon
summary: Arithmetic progression that mirrors MATLAB's colon operator.
description: `colon(start, stop)` and `colon(start, step, stop)` build row vectors that mirror the MATLAB colon operator.

name: compose
summary: Format values into MATLAB string arrays using printf-style placeholders.
description: `compose(formatSpec, A1, ..., An)` substitutes data into MATLAB-compatible `%` placeholders and returns the result as a string array.

name: cond
summary: Compute the matrix condition number with MATLAB-compatible norms.
description: `k = cond(A)` returns the condition number of matrix `A`, measuring how sensitive solutions to linear systems are to small perturbations in `A` or in the right-hand side.

name: conj
summary: Compute the complex conjugate of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `conj(x)` negates the imaginary component of every element in `x`; real values are returned unchanged. The builtin mirrors MathWorks MATLAB semantics for scalars, vectors, matrices, and N-D tensors.

name: containers.Map
summary: Create MATLAB-style dictionary objects that map keys to values.
description: `containers.Map` builds dictionary objects that associate unique keys with values. Keys can be character vectors, string scalars, or numeric scalars (double/int32/uint32/int64/uint64/logical).

name: containers.Map.isKey
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: containers.Map.keys
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: containers.Map.remove
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: containers.Map.subsasgn
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: containers.Map.subsref
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: containers.Map.values
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: contains
summary: Return logical values indicating whether text inputs contain specific patterns.
description: `contains(str, pattern)` returns a logical result indicating whether each element of `str` contains the corresponding text in `pattern`.

name: conv
summary: One-dimensional linear convolution with MATLAB-compatible padding.
description: `conv(a, b)` computes the one-dimensional linear convolution of the vectors `a` and `b`. The default padding mode returns the full convolution (`length(a) + length(b) - 1`).

name: conv2
summary: Two-dimensional convolution with MATLAB-compatible padding modes.
description: `conv2` performs two-dimensional linear convolution.

name: copyfile
summary: Copy files or folders with MATLAB-compatible status, diagnostic message, and message ID outputs.
description: `copyfile` duplicates files and folders. It mirrors MATLAB's behavior by returning a numeric status plus optional diagnostic text instead of throwing exceptions for filesystem failures.

name: corrcoef
summary: Compute Pearson correlation coefficients for the columns of matrices or paired data sets.
description: `corrcoef` returns the Pearson correlation coefficients between pairs of variables. Given a matrix, every column is treated as a separate variable and every row is an observation.

name: cos
summary: Cosine of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `y = cos(x)` evaluates the cosine of each element in `x`, interpreting angles in radians while preserving MATLABâs column-major layout and broadcasting rules.

name: cosh
summary: Hyperbolic cosine of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `Y = cosh(X)` computes the hyperbolic cosine of every element in `X`, extending naturally to complex values.

name: cov
summary: Compute covariance matrices for vectors, matrices, or paired data sets.
description: `cov` returns covariance matrices for numeric data. Columns represent variables and rows are observations.

name: csvread
summary: Read numeric data from a comma-separated text file.
description: `csvread(filename)` reads numeric data from a comma-separated text file and returns a dense double-precision matrix.

name: csvwrite
summary: Write numeric matrices to comma-separated text files using MATLAB-compatible offsets.
description: `csvwrite(filename, M)` writes a numeric matrix to a comma-separated text file.

name: Ctor.Ctor
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: ctranspose
summary: Swap the first two dimensions of arrays and conjugate complex values.
description: `B = ctranspose(A)` (or `B = A'`) flips the first two dimensions of `A` **and** conjugates complex values.

name: cummax
summary: Cumulative maximum and index tracking for scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `cummax(X)` computes the cumulative maximum of the elements in `X` along a chosen dimension. It also tracks where each running maximum occurs, mirroring MATLAB's two-output behaviour.

name: cummin
summary: Cumulative minimum and index tracking for scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `cummin(X)` computes the cumulative minimum of the elements in `X` along a chosen dimension. It also tracks where each running minimum occurs, mirroring MATLAB's two-output behaviour.

name: cumprod
summary: Cumulative product of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `cumprod(X)` multiplies elements cumulatively along a chosen dimension. The result has the same size as `X`, and each element stores the running product.

name: cumsum
summary: Cumulative sum of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `cumsum(X)` computes the cumulative sum of the elements in `X`. The result has the same size as `X` and each element stores the running total along a chosen dimension.

name: deal
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: deconv
summary: Polynomial (1-D sequence) deconvolution returning quotient and remainder.
description: `deconv(b, a)` performs one-dimensional polynomial long division. Given coefficient vectors `b` and `a`, it returns a quotient `q` and remainder `r` such that

name: delete
summary: Remove files using MATLAB-compatible wildcard expansion, array inputs, and error diagnostics.
description: `delete(filename)` removes files from disk, and `delete(obj)` invalidates handle objects or listeners.

name: det
summary: Compute the determinant of a square matrix.
description: `det(A)` returns the determinant of a real or complex square matrix `A`. Scalars behave like `det(1x1) = A(1,1)`, and the empty matrix (`[]`) has determinant `1`, matching MATLAB's convention.

name: diag
summary: Create diagonal matrices from vectors or extract diagonals from matrices.
description: `diag` either constructs a diagonal matrix from a vector (placing the vector on a specified diagonal) or extracts a diagonal from a matrix.

name: diff
summary: Forward finite differences of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `diff(X)` computes forward finite differences along the first dimension of `X` whose size exceeds 1. For vectors, this is simply the difference between adjacent elements.

name: dir
summary: Return file and folder information in a MATLAB-compatible struct array.
description: `dir` returns metadata for files and folders. Without arguments, it lists the current working directory.

name: disp
summary: Display value in the Command Window without returning output.
description: `disp` prints the contents of a variable to the Command Window without including the variable name.

name: dlmread
summary: Read numeric data from a delimiter-separated text file.
description: `dlmread(filename)` reads numeric data from an ASCII text file that uses a consistent delimiter between fields.

name: dlmwrite
summary: Write numeric matrices to delimiter-separated text files.
description: `dlmwrite(filename, M)` writes the numeric contents of `M` to a plain text file using a configurable delimiter.

name: dot
summary: Dot product (inner product) of matching tensors along a specified dimension.
description: `dot(A, B)` evaluates the inner product between matching slices of `A` and `B`. Inputs must have the same size, and complex vectors follow MATLAB's convention `sum(conj(A) .* B)`.

name: double
summary: Convert scalars, arrays, logical masks, and gpuArray values to double precision.
description: `double(X)` promotes scalars, arrays, complex values, logical masks, character data, and gpuArray handles to MATLABâs default double-precision (`float64`) representation while preserving shapes and column-major layout.

name: eig
summary: Eigenvalue decomposition with MATLAB-compatible multi-output forms.
description: `eig(A)` computes the eigenvalues of a square matrix `A`.

name: endsWith
summary: Return logical values indicating whether text inputs end with specific patterns.
description: `endsWith(str, pattern)` returns a logical result indicating whether each element of `str` ends with the corresponding text in `pattern`.

name: eq
summary: Element-wise equality comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `eq(A, B)` (or the infix `A == B`) performs an element-wise equality comparison. The result is a logical scalar when the broadcasted shape contains one element, or a logical array otherwise.

name: erase
summary: Remove substring occurrences from strings, character arrays, and cell arrays.
description: `erase(text, pattern)` removes every occurrence of `pattern` from `text`.

name: eraseBetween
summary: Delete text between boundary markers with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `eraseBetween(text, start, stop)` removes the portion of `text` that appears between two boundary markers. Boundaries can be substrings or numeric positions.

name: error
summary: Throw an exception with an identifier and a formatted diagnostic message.
description: `error` throws an exception immediately, unwinding the current execution frame and transferring control to the nearest `catch` block (or aborting the program if none exists).

name: exist
summary: Determine whether a variable, file, folder, built-in, or class exists.
description: `exist(name)` returns an integer code that identifies which kind of item named `name` is currently available. The codes match MATLAB:

name: exp
summary: Element-wise exponential of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = exp(X)` raises *e* to the power of every element in `X`. Results follow MATLAB semantics for scalars, vectors, matrices, logical arrays, character arrays, and complex inputs.

name: exp10
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: exp2
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: expm1
summary: Accurate element-wise computation of exp(x) - 1.
description: `Y = expm1(X)` evaluates `exp(X) - 1` element-wise while maintaining high accuracy for values of `X` that are close to zero.

name: extractBetween
summary: Extract substrings between boundary markers using MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `extractBetween(text, start, stop)` locates the substring that appears between two boundary markers.

name: eye
summary: Identity matrix or N-D identity tensor.
description: `eye` creates identity matrices (and higher-dimensional identity tensors) containing ones along the leading diagonal and zeros everywhere else.

name: factorial
summary: Element-wise factorial for non-negative integers with MATLAB-compatible NaN/Inf behaviour.
description: `factorial(X)` computes `X!` (the product of the integers from `1` to `X`) for every element of `X`.

name: fclose
summary: Close one file, multiple files, or all files opened with fopen.
description: `fclose` closes files that were previously opened with `fopen`. Pass a file identifier, an array of identifiers, or the keyword `'all'` to close the desired handles.

name: feof
summary: Query whether a file identifier is positioned at end-of-file.
description: `feof(fid)` reports whether the file position indicator associated with `fid` has reached the end of the file.

name: feval
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: fft
summary: Compute the discrete Fourier transform (DFT) of numeric or complex data.
description: `fft(X)` computes the discrete Fourier transform (DFT) of the input data. When `X` is a vector, `fft` returns the frequency-domain representation of the vector.

name: fft2
summary: Compute the two-dimensional discrete Fourier transform (DFT) of numeric or complex data.
description: `fft2(X)` computes the two-dimensional discrete Fourier transform (DFT) of `X`.

name: fftshift
summary: Shift zero-frequency components to the center of a spectrum.
description: `fftshift(X)` circularly shifts the output of an FFT so that the zero-frequency component moves to the center of each transformed dimension.

name: fgets
summary: Read the next line from a file, including newline characters.
description: `fgets(fid)` returns the next line from the text file associated with `fid`, preserving any newline characters that terminate the line.

name: fieldnames
summary: List the field names of scalar structs or struct arrays.
description: `fieldnames(S)` returns a column cell array of character vectors containing the field names defined on `S`.

name: fileread
summary: Read the entire contents of a text file into a 1-by-N character vector.
description: `fileread(filename)` loads the complete contents of a text file into memory and returns a row vector of characters that mirrors MATLAB's behaviour.

name: filewrite
summary: Write text or raw bytes to a file.
description: `filewrite(filename, data)` writes text or raw byte content to a file, returning the number of bytes written.

name: fill
summary: Create arrays filled with a constant value.
description: `fill(value, size, ...)` constructs dense MATLAB arrays whose entries are all the supplied `value`.

name: filter
summary: Apply an IIR/FIR digital filter to scalars, vectors, or tensors.
description: `filter` evaluates the causal linear difference equation

name: filter2
summary: Apply a 2-D correlation or convolution with MATLAB-compatible sizing.
description: `filter2(H, X)` performs a 2-D correlation of the image (or matrix) `X` with the kernel `H`.

name: find
summary: Locate indices and values of nonzero elements.
description: `find(X)` returns the indices of nonzero elements of `X`. With a single output it produces MATLAB's 1-based linear indices.

name: fix
summary: Round scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors toward zero.
description: `fix(X)` removes the fractional part of each element in `X` by rounding toward zero. Positive numbers behave like `floor`, negatives behave like `ceil`, and zeros stay zero.

name: flip
summary: Reverse the order of elements along specific dimensions.
description: `flip(A)` reverses the order of elements in `A` along one or more dimensions. With no dimension argument, RunMat (like MATLAB) flips along the first dimension whose extent is greater than one.

name: fliplr
summary: Flip an array left-to-right along the second dimension.
description: `fliplr(A)` mirrors `A` across its vertical axis, reversing the column order (dimension 2).

name: flipud
summary: Flip an array up-to-down along the first dimension.
description: `flipud(A)` mirrors `A` across its horizontal axis, reversing the order of rows (dimension 1).

name: floor
summary: Round values toward negative infinity.
description: `floor(X)` rounds each element of `X` toward negative infinity, returning the greatest integer less than or equal to the input.

name: fopen
summary: Open a file and obtain a MATLAB-compatible file identifier.
description: `fopen` opens a file and returns a numeric file identifier (`fid`) that other I/O functions use.

name: fprintf
summary: Write formatted text to files or standard streams.
description: `fprintf` formats data according to a printf-style template and writes the result to a file, standard output (`stdout`), or standard error (`stderr`).

name: fread
summary: Read binary data from a file identifier.
description: `fread` reads binary data from a file identifier returned by `fopen`.

name: fspecial
summary: Generate classical 2-D correlation kernels used in MATLAB image processing workflows.
description: `fspecial(type, ...)` constructs well-known 2-D filter kernels such as averaging, Gaussian, Laplacian, Sobel, Prewitt, motion blur, Laplacian of Gaussian, unsharp masking, and disk (pillbox) filters.

name: fwrite
summary: Write binary data to a file identifier.
description: `fwrite` writes binary data to a file identifier obtained from `fopen`.

name: gamma
summary: Element-wise gamma function for scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = gamma(X)` evaluates the Euler gamma function element-by-element.

name: gather
summary: Transfer gpuArray data back to host memory, recursively handling cells, structs, and objects.
description: `gather(X)` copies data that resides on the GPU or in another distributed storage back into host memory.

name: ge
summary: Element-wise greater-than-or-equal comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `ge(A, B)` (or the infix `A >= B`) performs an element-wise greater-than-or-equal comparison.

name: genpath
summary: Generate a MATLAB-style search path string for a folder tree.
description: `genpath` walks a folder tree and returns a character vector that lists the folder and every subfolder in depth-first order.

name: get.p
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: getenv
summary: Query environment variables as character vectors, strings, or structures.
description: `getenv` reads environment variables that are visible to the current process.

name: getfield
summary: Access a field or property from structs, struct arrays, or MATLAB-style objects.
description: `value = getfield(S, field)` returns the contents of `S.field`.

name: getmethod
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: gpuArray
summary: Move data to the GPU and return a gpuArray handle.
description: `gpuArray(X)` moves MATLAB values onto the active GPU and returns a handle that the rest of the runtime can execute on.

name: gpuDevice
summary: Return information about the active GPU device/provider.
description: `info = gpuDevice()` queries the active accelerator provider and returns a MATLAB struct that describes the GPU (or GPU-like backend) that RunMat is currently using.

name: gpuInfo
summary: Return a formatted status string that describes the active GPU provider.
description: `gpuInfo()` returns a concise, human-readable string that summarises the active GPU acceleration provider.

name: gt
summary: Element-wise greater-than comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `gt(A, B)` (or the infix `A > B`) performs an element-wise greater-than comparison. The result is a logical scalar when the broadcasted shape contains one element, or a logical array otherwise.

name: hist
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: histcounts
summary: Count observations in numeric arrays using configurable histogram bins.
description: `histcounts` tallies the number of elements that fall within each histogram bin.

name: histcounts2
summary: Count paired observations into two-dimensional histogram bins.
description: `histcounts2(X, Y)` bins paired observations from `X` and `Y` into a rectangular two-dimensional histogram.

name: horzcat
summary: Concatenate inputs horizontally (dimension 2) just like MATLAB square brackets.
description: `horzcat(A1, A2, â¦)` horizontally concatenates its inputs, matching the behaviour of MATLAB's square-bracket syntax `[A1 A2 â¦]`.

name: hypot
summary: Element-wise Euclidean norm sqrt(x.^2 + y.^2) with MATLAB-compatible broadcasting.
description: `z = hypot(x, y)` computes the element-wise Euclidean norm `sqrt(|x|.^2 + |y|.^2)` with overflow-resistant arithmetic.

name: ifft
summary: Inverse discrete Fourier transform with optional length, dimension, and symmetric flag.
description: `ifft(X)` performs the inverse discrete Fourier transform (IDFT) of the data in `X`. For vectors, the result is a time-domain sequence whose FFT equals the original input.

name: ifft2
summary: Compute the two-dimensional inverse discrete Fourier transform (IDFT) of numeric or complex data.
description: `ifft2(X)` computes the two-dimensional inverse discrete Fourier transform (IDFT) of `X`.

name: ifftshift
summary: Undo fftshift by moving the zero-frequency component back to the origin.
description: `ifftshift(X)` circularly shifts data so that the DC (zero-frequency) component returns to index 1 along each transformed dimension.

name: imag
summary: Extract the imaginary component of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `imag(x)` returns the imaginary component of every element in `x`. Complex inputs yield their imaginary part, while real inputs produce zero-valued results of matching shape.

name: imfilter
summary: Apply linear filters with MATLAB-compatible padding semantics.
description: `imfilter` applies N-D linear filters (correlation or convolution) to numeric or logical arrays.

name: ind2sub
summary: Convert MATLAB column-major linear indices into per-dimension subscript arrays.
description: `ind2sub(siz, idx)` converts MATLAB's 1-based column-major linear indices back into the individual subscripts for each dimension specified in `siz`.

name: intersect
summary: Return common elements or rows across arrays with MATLAB-compatible ordering and index outputs.
description: `intersect(A, B)` computes the set intersection of `A` and `B`.

name: inv
summary: Compute the inverse of a square matrix.
description: `X = inv(A)` returns the matrix inverse of a square, full-rank matrix `A`. The result satisfies `A * X = eye(size(A))` within round-off.

name: ipermute
summary: Reorder array dimensions using the inverse of a permutation vector.
description: `ipermute(A, order)` reverses the dimension reordering performed by `permute(A, order)`. It is equivalent to `permute(A, invOrder)`, where `invOrder(order(i)) = i`.

name: isa
summary: Test whether a value belongs to a specified MATLAB class or abstract category.
description: `isa(x, T)` returns logical `true` when the value `x` is a member of the MATLAB class or abstract category identified by `T`.

name: ischar
summary: Return true when a value is a MATLAB character array.
description: `tf = ischar(x)` returns logical `true` when `x` is a MATLAB character array (a char row vector or matrix) and logical `false` otherwise.

name: isempty
summary: Return true when an array has zero elements, matching MATLAB semantics.
description: `isempty(A)` returns logical `true` when the MATLAB value `A` contains zero elements.

name: isfield
summary: Test whether a struct or struct array defines specific field names.
description: `tf = isfield(S, name)` returns a logical value that indicates whether the struct `S` defines the field `name`.

name: isfinite
summary: Return a logical mask indicating which elements of the input are finite.
description: `mask = isfinite(x)` returns a logical scalar or array indicating which elements of `x` are finite (not `NaN`, `+Inf`, or `-Inf`).

name: ishermitian
summary: Determine whether a matrix is Hermitian or skew-Hermitian.
description: `ishermitian(A)` returns logical `true` when `A` equals its conjugate transpose (`A == A'`). The builtin works with real and complex matrices, logical arrays, and scalars.

name: isinf
summary: Return a logical mask indicating which elements of the input are ±Inf.
description: `mask = isinf(x)` returns a logical scalar or array indicating which elements of `x` are positive or negative infinity.

name: islogical
summary: Return true when a value uses logical storage.
description: `tf = islogical(x)` returns a logical scalar that is `true` when `x` is stored as MATLAB logical data (either a scalar logical or an N-D logical array).

name: ismatrix
summary: Return true when an array has at most two dimensions (m-by-n, including vectors and scalars).
description: `ismatrix(A)` returns logical `true` when the input has two dimensions (`m`-by-`n`) and logical `false` otherwise.

name: ismember
summary: Identify array elements or rows that appear in another array while returning first-match indices.
description: `ismember(A, B)` compares the elements (or rows) of `A` against `B` and returns a logical array marking which members of `A` are present in `B`.

name: isnan
summary: Return a logical mask indicating which elements of the input are NaN.
description: `mask = isnan(x)` returns a logical scalar or array indicating which elements of `x` are IEEE NaN (Not-a-Number) values.

name: isnumeric
summary: Return true when a value is stored as numeric data.
description: `tf = isnumeric(x)` returns a logical scalar that is `true` when `x` stores numeric data and `false` otherwise.

name: isreal
summary: Return true when a value uses real storage without an imaginary component.
description: `tf = isreal(x)` returns a logical scalar that is `true` when the value `x` is stored without an imaginary component, and `false` otherwise.

name: isscalar
summary: Return true when a value has exactly one element and unit dimensions.
description: `isscalar(A)` returns logical `true` when an input has exactly one element and every visible dimension equals one.

name: issorted
summary: Determine whether an array is already sorted.
description: `issorted(A)` checks whether the elements of `A` already appear in sorted order.

name: isstring
summary: Return true when a value is a MATLAB string array.
description: `tf = isstring(x)` returns a logical scalar `true` when `x` is a MATLAB string array (including string scalars and empty string arrays) and logical `false` otherwise.

name: issymmetric
summary: Test whether a matrix is symmetric or skew-symmetric.
description: `issymmetric(A)` returns logical `true` when a numeric or logical matrix `A` is symmetric about its main diagonal (`A == A.'`) and `false` otherwise.

name: isvalid
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: isvector
summary: Return true when an array is 1-by-N or N-by-1 (including scalars).
description: `isvector(A)` returns logical `true` when the input is 1-by-`N` or `N`-by-1 (including scalars) and has at most two dimensions.

name: join
summary: Combine text across a specified dimension inserting delimiters between elements.
description: `join` concatenates text along a chosen dimension of a string array or a cell array of character vectors.

name: jsondecode
summary: Parse UTF-8 JSON text into MATLAB-compatible RunMat values.
description: `jsondecode` converts UTF-8 JSON text into MATLAB-compatible data.

name: jsonencode
summary: Serialize MATLAB values to UTF-8 JSON text.
description: `jsonencode` converts MATLAB values into UTF-8 JSON text.

name: kron
summary: Compute the Kronecker (tensor) product of two arrays.
description: `kron(A, B)` forms the Kronecker (tensor) product of arrays `A` and `B`.

name: ldivide
summary: Element-wise left division (B ./ A) with MATLAB-compatible implicit expansion.
description: `ldivide(A, B)` (operator form `A .\ B`) divides each element of `B` by the corresponding element of `A`, delivering MATLAB-compatible left-division semantics.

name: le
summary: Element-wise less-than-or-equal comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `le(A, B)` (or the infix `A <= B`) performs an element-wise less-than-or-equal comparison. The result is a logical scalar when the broadcasted shape contains one element, or a logical array otherwise.

name: length
summary: Return the length of the largest dimension of scalars, vectors, matrices, and N-D arrays.
description: `length(A)` returns the length of the largest dimension of `A`.

name: linsolve
summary: Solve A * X = B with structural hints such as LT, UT, POSDEF, or TRANSA.
description: `X = linsolve(A, B)` solves the linear system `A * X = B`.

name: linspace
summary: Linearly spaced vector.
description: `linspace(a, b, n)` returns `n` linearly spaced points between the start point `a` and the end point `b`, inclusive. When `n` is omitted, MATLAB (and RunMat) default to 100 points.

name: ln
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: load
summary: Load variables from a MAT-file.
description: `load` reads variables from a MAT-file (Level-5 layout) and brings them into the current workspace.

name: log
summary: Natural logarithm of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = log(X)` computes the natural logarithm of every element in `X`, extending MATLAB semantics to real, logical, character, and complex inputs.

name: log10
summary: Base-10 logarithm of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = log10(X)` computes the base-10 logarithm of every element in `X`, following MATLAB's numeric semantics for real, logical, character, and complex inputs.

name: log1p
summary: Accurate element-wise computation of log(1 + x).
description: `Y = log1p(X)` evaluates `log(1 + X)` element-wise with high accuracy for values of `X` close to zero.

name: log2
summary: Base-2 logarithm of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = log2(X)` computes the base-2 logarithm of every element in `X`, following MATLAB's semantics for real, logical, character, and complex inputs.

name: logical
summary: Convert scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values to logical outputs.
description: `logical(X)` converts numeric, logical, character, and gpuArray inputs into MATLAB logical values (booleans). Any non-zero (or `NaN`/`Inf`) element maps to `true`, while zero maps to `false`.

name: logspace
summary: Logarithmically spaced vector.
description: `logspace(a, b, n)` returns `n` points that are equally spaced on a logarithmic scale between `10^a` and `10^b`. When `n` is omitted, MATLAB (and RunMat) default to 50 points.

name: lower
summary: Convert strings, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors to lowercase.
description: `lower(text)` converts every alphabetic character in `text` to lowercase. It accepts string scalars, string arrays, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors, mirroring MATLAB behaviour.

name: ls
summary: List files and folders in the current directory or matching a wildcard pattern.
description: `ls` lists the contents of a directory. Without inputs, it shows the files and folders in the current working directory.

name: lt
summary: Element-wise less-than comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `lt(A, B)` (or the infix `A < B`) performs an element-wise less-than comparison. The result is a logical scalar when the broadcasted shape contains one element, or a logical array otherwise.

name: lu
summary: LU decomposition with partial pivoting.
description: `lu(A)` computes the LU factorization of a real or complex matrix `A` using partial pivoting. It exposes the same calling forms as MATLAB:

name: make_anon

name: make_handle

name: mat2cell
summary: Split arrays into cell-array blocks.
description: `mat2cell` partitions an array along each dimension according to vectors of block sizes and returns those blocks inside a cell array.

name: max

description: `max` returns the largest values in its input while preserving MATLAB semantics for reductions, elementwise comparisons, NaN handling, complex magnitude comparisons, and linear indexing.

name: mean
summary: Average elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `mean(x)` computes the arithmetic mean of scalars, vectors, matrices, and higher-dimensional tensors. When no dimension is supplied, the reduction runs along the first non-singleton dimension.

name: median
summary: Median of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `median(x)` returns the middle value of scalars, vectors, matrices, and higher-dimensional tensors. When no dimension is supplied, the reduction runs along the first non-singleton dimension.

name: mesh
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: meshgrid
summary: Generate coordinate matrices for 2-D and 3-D grids.
description: `meshgrid` turns one-, two-, or three-dimensional vectors into coordinate arrays that span a rectangular grid, mirroring MathWorks MATLAB behaviour exactly.

name: min
summary: Return the minimum elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `min` finds the smallest values in its input while preserving MATLAB semantics for reductions, elementwise comparisons, NaN handling, complex magnitude comparisons, and linear indexing.

name: minus
summary: Element-wise subtraction with MATLAB-compatible implicit expansion.
description: `minus(A, B)` (or the operator form `A - B`) subtracts corresponding elements of `B` from `A`, honouring MATLAB's implicit expansion rules so that scalars and singleton dimensions broadcast automatically.

name: mkdir
summary: Create folders with MATLAB-compatible status, message, and message ID outputs.
description: `mkdir` creates new folders on disk.

name: mldivide
summary: Solve A * X = B using MATLAB-compatible left division.

name: mod
summary: MATLAB-compatible modulus a - b .* floor(a./b) with support for complex values and broadcasting.
description: `C = mod(A, B)` returns the modulus after division such that `C` has the same sign as `B` and satisfies `A = B.*Q + C` with `Q = floor(A./B)`.

name: movefile
summary: Move or rename files and folders with MATLAB-compatible status, message, and message ID outputs.
description: `movefile` renames files and folders or moves them to a new location.

name: mpower
summary: Matrix power with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `C = mpower(A, B)` evaluates the matrix power `A^B`.

name: mrdivide
summary: Solve X * B = A using MATLAB-compatible right division.
description: `X = A / B` (or `mrdivide(A, B)`) solves the right-sided linear system `X * B = A`. When `B` is square and nonsingular the solution matches `A * inv(B)`.

name: mtimes
summary: Matrix multiplication with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `mtimes(A, B)` implements MATLAB's matrix multiplication operator (`A * B`).

name: ndims
summary: Return the number of dimensions of scalars, vectors, matrices, and N-D arrays.
description: `ndims(A)` returns the number of dimensions (rank) of `A`, following MATLAB conventions.

name: ne
summary: Element-wise inequality comparison for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray inputs.
description: `ne(A, B)` (or the infix `A ~= B`) performs an element-wise inequality comparison. The result is a logical scalar when the broadcasted shape contains one element, or a logical array otherwise.

name: new_handle_object
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: new_object
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: nnz
summary: Count the number of nonzero elements in an array with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `nnz(X)` returns the number of elements of `X` that are nonzero.

name: norm
summary: Vector and matrix norms with MATLAB semantics.
description: `norm(X)` returns the magnitude of vectors and matrices.

name: not
summary: Element-wise logical negation for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values.
description: `not(X)` inverts the logical interpretation of every element in `X`. Values that evaluate to `true` become `false`, and vice versa.

name: notify
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: num2str
summary: Format numeric scalars, vectors, and matrices as character arrays.
description: `num2str(x)` converts numeric scalars, vectors, and matrices into a character array where each row of `x` becomes a row of text.

name: numel
summary: Count the number of elements in scalars, vectors, matrices, and N-D arrays.
description: `numel(A)` returns the number of elements contained in `A`, matching MATLAB semantics for dense arrays, logical arrays, cell arrays, structs, strings, and character arrays.

name: ones
summary: Create arrays filled with ones.
description: `ones` creates arrays filled with ones. RunMat mirrors MATLAB semantics across the scalar, vector, matrix, and N-D forms, including `'like'` and `'logical'` options.

name: or
summary: Element-wise logical OR for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values.
description: `or(A, B)` returns the element-wise logical OR of its inputs. Any non-zero value (including `NaN`) evaluates to `true`.

name: orderfields
summary: Reorder structure field definitions alphabetically or using a supplied order.
description: `orderfields(S)` reorders the field definitions of a scalar struct or struct array. By default the fields are sorted alphabetically.

name: pad
summary: Pad strings, character arrays, and cell arrays to a target length.
description: `pad` adds characters to the beginning, end, or both sides of strings so that each element reaches a specified length.

name: pagefun
summary: Apply MATLAB operators page-by-page across higher-dimensional arrays.
description: `pagefun(func, A, B, â¦)` applies the MATLAB operator referenced by `func` to every page of the supplied arrays.

name: path
summary: Query or replace the MATLAB search path used by RunMat.
description: `path` reads or rewrites the MATLAB search path string that RunMat uses when resolving scripts, functions, and data files.

name: pause
summary: Suspend execution until a key press or specified duration.
description: `pause` suspends execution and mirrors MATLAB's timing semantics:

name: permute
summary: Reorder the dimensions of arrays, tensors, logical masks, and gpuArray values.
description: `permute(A, order)` rearranges the dimensions of `A` to match the order specified by the integer vector `order`.

name: pinv
summary: Compute the Moore–Penrose pseudoinverse of a matrix using SVD.
description: `X = pinv(A)` returns the MooreâPenrose pseudoinverse of `A`.

name: PkgF.foo
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: PkgG.foo

name: plot
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: plus
summary: Element-wise addition with MATLAB-compatible implicit expansion.
description: `plus(A, B)` (or the operator form `A + B`) adds corresponding elements of `A` and `B`, honouring MATLAB's implicit expansion rules so that scalars and singleton dimensions broadcast automatically.

name: Point.move
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: Point.origin
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: polyder
summary: Differentiate polynomials, products, and ratios with MATLAB-compatible coefficient vectors.
description: `polyder` differentiates polynomials represented by their coefficient vectors. The coefficients follow MATLABâs convention: the first element corresponds to the highest power of `x`.

name: polyfit
summary: Fit an n-th degree polynomial to data points with MATLAB-compatible outputs.
description: `polyfit(x, y, n)` returns the coefficients of an `n`-th degree polynomial that fits the samples `(x, y)` in a least-squares sense.

name: polyint
summary: Integrate polynomial coefficient vectors and append a constant of integration.
description: `polyint(p)` returns the polynomial that integrates the coefficient vector `p` once, appending the constant of integration at the end of the coefficient list.

name: polyval
summary: Evaluate a polynomial at given points with MATLAB-compatible options.
description: `polyval(p, x)` evaluates the polynomial defined by the coefficient vector `p` at every element of `x`.

name: pow
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: pow2
summary: Compute 2.^X or scale mantissas by binary exponents.
description: `Y = pow2(X)` computes the element-wise power-of-two `2.^X`. With two inputs, `Z = pow2(F, E)` returns the element-wise product `F .* 2.^E`, mirroring MATLAB's `ldexp`-style scaling.

name: power
summary: Element-wise power with MATLAB-compatible broadcasting and complex support.
description: `Y = power(A, B)` (or `A .^ B`) raises each element of `A` to the corresponding element of `B` using MATLAB's implicit-expansion rules.

name: prod
summary: Multiply elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `prod(X)` multiplies the elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, and higher-dimensional tensors. When no dimension is supplied, the reduction runs along the first non-singleton dimension.

name: pwd
summary: Return the absolute path to the folder where RunMat is currently executing.
description: `pwd` returns the absolute path of the folder where RunMat is executing.

name: qr
summary: QR factorization with optional column pivoting and economy-size outputs.
description: `qr(A)` computes an orthogonal (or unitary)âupper-triangular factorization of a real or complex matrix `A`.

name: rand
summary: Uniform random numbers on (0, 1).
description: `rand` produces uniformly distributed pseudorandom numbers over the open interval (0, 1).

name: randi
summary: Uniform random integers with inclusive bounds.
description: `randi` draws uniformly distributed random integers from an inclusive range.

name: randn
summary: Standard normal random numbers.
description: `randn` draws pseudorandom samples from the standard normal distribution (`Î¼ = 0`, `Ï = 1`).

name: randperm
summary: Random permutations of 1:n.
description: `randperm(n)` returns a uniformly random permutation of the integers `1:n`. `randperm(n, k)` selects `k` unique integers from `1:n` without replacement.

name: range
summary: Compute the difference between the maximum and minimum values.
description: `range(X)` returns the span (maximum minus minimum) of the elements in `X`. For arrays, the calculation happens along the first non-singleton dimension unless you specify one.

name: rank
summary: Compute the numerical rank of a matrix using SVD with MATLAB-compatible tolerance handling.
description: `r = rank(A)` returns the numerical rank of a real or complex matrix `A`.

name: rcond
summary: Estimate the reciprocal condition number of a square matrix.
description: `rc = rcond(A)` returns an estimate of the reciprocal of the condition number of a square matrix `A` in the 1-norm.

name: rdivide
summary: Element-wise division with MATLAB-compatible implicit expansion.
description: `rdivide(A, B)` (or the operator form `A ./ B`) divides corresponding elements of `A` and `B`, honouring MATLAB's implicit expansion rules so that scalars and singleton dimensions broadcast automatically.

name: read
summary: Read numeric or text data from a TCP/IP client.
description: `read(t)` consumes data waiting on the TCP/IP client returned by `tcpclient` (or `accept`).

name: readline
summary: Read ASCII text until the terminator from a TCP/IP client.
description: `readline(t)` reads ASCII text from the remote host associated with the MATLAB-compatible `tcpclient` struct `t`.

name: readmatrix
summary: Import numeric data from delimited text files into a RunMat matrix.
description: `readmatrix(filename)` reads numeric data from text or delimited files and returns a dense double-precision matrix.

name: real
summary: Extract the real part of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `real(x)` returns the real component of each element in `x`. Real inputs are passed through unchanged, while complex inputs discard their imaginary component.

name: regexp
summary: Regular expression matching with MATLAB-compatible outputs.
description: `regexp(text, pattern)` locates regular expression matches inside character vectors, string scalars, string arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors.

name: regexpi
summary: Case-insensitive regular expression matching with MATLAB-compatible outputs.
description: `regexpi(text, pattern)` evaluates regular expression matches while ignoring case by default.

name: regexprep
summary: Regular expression replacement with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `regexprep(str, pattern, replacement)` searches `str` for regular expression matches and replaces each match with the specified replacement text.

name: rem
summary: MATLAB-compatible remainder a - b .* fix(a./b) with support for complex values and broadcasting.
description: `C = rem(A, B)` returns the remainder after division with the quotient rounded toward zero: `C = A - B .* fix(A ./ B)`.

name: replace
summary: Replace substring occurrences in strings, character arrays, and cell arrays.
description: `replace(str, old, new)` substitutes every occurrence of `old` found in `str` with `new`.

name: repmat
summary: Replicate arrays by tiling an input across one or more dimensions.
description: `repmat(A, reps)` tiles the array `A` so that it repeats according to `reps`.

name: reshape
summary: Rearrange the dimensions of an array without changing its data.
description: `reshape(A, newSize)` returns the elements of `A` with a different dimensional layout while preserving column-major ordering.

name: rethrow
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: rmdir
summary: Remove folders with MATLAB-compatible status, message, and message ID outputs.
description: `rmdir` removes folders from the filesystem.

name: rmfield
summary: Remove one or more fields from scalar structs or struct arrays.
description: `S2 = rmfield(S, name)` returns a copy of `S` with the field `name` removed. The builtin accepts additional field names, string arrays, or cell arrays of names to delete several fields in one call.

name: rmpath
summary: Remove folders from the MATLAB search path used by RunMat.
description: `rmpath` removes folders from the MATLAB search path that RunMat consults when resolving functions, scripts, classes, and data files.

name: rng
summary: Seed, shuffle, and query the global random number generator.
description: `rng` queries or reconfigures the global pseudorandom number generator that powers `rand`, `randn`, `randi`, and `randperm`.

name: roots
summary: Compute the roots of a polynomial specified by its coefficients.
description: `roots(p)` returns the zeros of the polynomial whose coefficients are stored in `p`, with coefficients ordered from the highest power of `x` to the constant term.

name: rot90
summary: Rotate matrices and N-D arrays by multiples of 90 degrees.
description: `rot90(A)` rotates the matrix `A` by 90 degrees counterclockwise. A second argument specifies additional 90-degree turns (positive values rotate counterclockwise, negative values clockwise).

name: round
summary: Round values to the nearest integers, decimal places, or significant digits.
description: `round(X)` rounds numeric values to the nearest integers using MATLAB-compatible half-away-from-zero semantics.

name: save
summary: Persist workspace variables to a MAT-file.
description: `save` writes variables from the current workspace to a MAT-file on disk.

name: savepath
summary: Persist the current MATLAB search path to pathdef.m with status outputs.
description: `savepath` writes the current MATLAB search path to a `pathdef.m` file so that future sessions can restore the same ordering.

name: scatter

name: scatter3
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: set.p
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: setdiff
summary: Return the values that appear in the first input but not the second.
description: `setdiff(A, B)` returns the set of values (or rows) that appear in `A` but not in `B`. Results are unique, and the function can operate in sorted or stable order as well as row mode.

name: setenv
summary: Set or clear environment variables with MATLAB-compatible status outputs.
description: `setenv` updates the process environment. Provide a variable name and value to create or modify an entry, or pass an empty value to remove the variable.

name: setfield
summary: Assign into struct fields, struct arrays, or MATLAB-style object properties.
description: `S = setfield(S, field, value)` returns a copy of the struct (or object) with `field` assigned to `value`.

name: Shape.area
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: sign
summary: Sign of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors with real or complex values.
description: `y = sign(x)` returns the sign of each element of `x`. Real inputs become `-1`, `0`, or `1` depending on their value, while complex inputs are normalised to unit magnitude (`x ./ abs(x)`).

name: sin
summary: Sine of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `y = sin(x)` evaluates the sine of each element in `x`, using radians and preserving MATLABâs column-major layout and broadcasting rules.

name: single
summary: Convert scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values to single precision.
description: `single(X)` converts scalars, arrays, complex values, characters, logical inputs, and gpuArray handles into single-precision (`float32`) values while preserving MATLAB's column-major shapes.

name: sinh
summary: Hyperbolic sine of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `Y = sinh(X)` computes the hyperbolic sine of every element in `X`, treating angles as real numbers and extending naturally to complex values.

name: size
summary: Get the dimensions of scalars, vectors, matrices, and N-D arrays.
description: `size(A)` reports the length of every dimension of `A`. The return value is always a row vector describing the current shape, with scalars reported as `1Ã1`.

name: sort
summary: Sort scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors along a dimension, with optional index outputs.
description: `sort` orders the elements of its input along a chosen dimension.

name: sortrows
summary: Sort matrix rows lexicographically with optional column and direction control.
description: `sortrows` reorders the rows of a matrix (or character array) so they appear in lexicographic order.

name: split
summary: Split strings, character arrays, and cell arrays into substrings using delimiters.
description: `split(text)` breaks text into substrings separated by delimiters.

name: sprintf
summary: Format data into a character vector using printf-style placeholders.
description: `sprintf(formatSpec, A1, ..., An)` formats data into a character row vector.

name: sqrt
summary: Element-wise square root of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `Y = sqrt(X)` computes the principal square root of every element in `X`. Results follow MATLAB semantics for scalars, vectors, matrices, logical arrays, character arrays, and complex inputs.

name: squeeze
summary: Remove singleton dimensions while preserving MATLAB row/column semantics.
description: `squeeze(A)` removes singleton (dimension size equal to one) dimensions from `A`.

name: startsWith
summary: Return logical values indicating whether text inputs start with specific patterns.
description: `startsWith(str, pattern)` returns a logical result indicating whether each element of `str` begins with the corresponding text in `pattern`.

name: std
summary: Standard deviation of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors with MATLAB-compatible options.
description: `std(x)` measures the spread of the elements in `x`. By default RunMat matches MATLABâs sample definition (dividing by `n-1`) and works along the first non-singleton dimension.

name: str2double
summary: Convert strings, character arrays, or cell arrays of text into doubles.
description: `str2double` converts text representations of numbers into double-precision values. It accepts string scalars, string arrays, character vectors, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors.

name: strcat
summary: Concatenate strings, character arrays, or cell arrays of character vectors element-wise.
description: `strcat` horizontally concatenates text inputs element-wise.

name: strcmp
summary: Compare text inputs for exact matches (case-sensitive).
description: `strcmp(a, b)` returns logical `true` when two pieces of text match exactly and `false` otherwise.

name: strcmpi
summary: Compare text inputs for equality without considering case.
description: `strcmpi(a, b)` compares text values without considering letter case. It returns logical `true` when inputs match case-insensitively and `false` otherwise.

name: strfind
summary: Return the starting indices of pattern matches in text inputs.
description: `k = strfind(str, pattern)` returns the starting indices of every occurrence of `pattern` inside `str`.

name: string
summary: Convert numeric, logical, and text inputs into MATLAB string arrays.
description: `string(x)` converts scalars, arrays, and text-like inputs into MATLAB string arrays whose elements are string scalars.

name: string.empty
summary: Construct an empty string array with MATLAB-compatible dimensions.
description: `string.empty` constructs an empty string array.

name: strings
summary: Preallocate string arrays filled with empty text scalars using MATLAB-compatible size syntax.
description: `strings` creates string arrays whose elements are empty string scalars (`""`).

name: strip
summary: Remove leading and trailing characters from strings, character arrays, and cell arrays.
description: `strip(text)` removes consecutive whitespace characters from the beginning and end of `text`.

name: strjoin
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: strlength
summary: Count characters in string arrays, character arrays, or cell arrays of character vectors.
description: `strlength(str)` counts how many characters appear in each element of text inputs.

name: strncmp
summary: Compare text inputs for equality up to N leading characters (case-sensitive).
description: `strncmp(A, B, N)` compares text values element-wise and returns logical `true` when the first `N` characters of the corresponding elements are identical. Comparisons are case-sensitive and respect MATLAB's implicit expansion rules across strings, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors.

name: strrep
summary: Replace substring occurrences with MATLAB-compatible semantics.
description: `strrep(str, old, new)` replaces every non-overlapping instance of the substring `old` that appears in `str` with the text provided in `new`.

name: strtrim
summary: Remove leading and trailing whitespace from strings, character arrays, and cell arrays.
description: `strtrim(text)` removes leading and trailing whitespace characters from `text`.

name: struct
summary: Create scalar structs or struct arrays from name/value pairs.
description: `S = struct(...)` creates scalar structs or struct arrays by pairing field names with values.

name: sub2ind
summary: Convert N-D subscripts into MATLAB-style column-major linear indices.
description: `sub2ind(sz, s1, s2, ...)` converts row/column (or higher-dimensional) subscripts into MATLAB's column-major linear indexing form.

name: subsasgn
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: subsref
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: sum
summary: Sum elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors.
description: `sum(X)` adds together elements of scalars, vectors, matrices, and higher-dimensional tensors. When no dimension is supplied, the reduction runs along the first non-singleton dimension.

name: surf
summary: Runtime builtin function

name: svd
summary: Singular value decomposition with MATLAB-compatible economy and vector options.
description: `svd(A)` computes the singular value decomposition of a real or complex matrix `A`.

name: symrcm
summary: Compute the symmetric reverse Cuthill-McKee permutation that reduces matrix bandwidth.
description: `r = symrcm(A)` returns a permutation vector that reorders a symmetric (or structurally symmetric) matrix to reduce its bandwidth.

name: tan
summary: Tangent of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `y = tan(x)` computes the tangent of every element in `x`, interpreting each input value in radians.

name: tanh
summary: Hyperbolic tangent of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors (element-wise).
description: `y = tanh(x)` evaluates the hyperbolic tangent of each element in `x`, preserving MATLAB's column-major layout and broadcasting rules across scalars, arrays, and tensors.

name: tcpclient
summary: Open a TCP client socket that connects to MATLAB-compatible servers.
description: `tcpclient(host, port)` opens a TCP/IP connection to a remote server and returns a MATLAB-compatible struct that mirrors the `tcpclient` object.

name: tcpserver
summary: Create a TCP server that listens for MATLAB-compatible client connections.
description: `tcpserver(address, port)` creates a TCP/IP listener that waits for clients and exposes MATLAB-compatible properties describing the socket.

name: tempdir
summary: Return the absolute path to the system temporary folder.
description: `tempdir` returns the absolute path of the operating system's temporary folder.

name: tempname
summary: Return a unique temporary file path.
description: `tempname` returns a unique path that you can reserve for a temporary file or folder. By default it chooses the system temporary directory.

name: tic
summary: Start a stopwatch timer and optionally return a handle for toc.
description: `tic` starts a high-resolution stopwatch. Calls to `toc` report the elapsed time in seconds.

name: timeit
summary: Measure the execution time of a zero-argument function handle.
description: `t = timeit(f)` evaluates the zero-argument function handle `f` repeatedly and returns the median runtime (in seconds).

name: times
summary: Element-wise multiplication with MATLAB-compatible implicit expansion.
description: `times(A, B)` (or the operator form `A .* B`) multiplies corresponding elements of `A` and `B`, honouring MATLAB's implicit expansion rules so that scalars and singleton dimensions broadcast automatically.

name: toc
summary: Read the elapsed time since the most recent tic or an explicit handle.
description: `toc` returns the elapsed wall-clock time in seconds since the last matching `tic`, or since the `tic` handle you pass as an argument.

name: trace
summary: Sum the diagonal elements of matrices and matrix-like tensors.
description: `trace(A)` returns the sum of the elements on the main diagonal of `A`. The result matches MATLAB for scalars, vectors, rectangular matrices, logical masks, and complex inputs.

name: transpose
summary: Swap the first two dimensions of arrays without conjugating complex values.
description: `B = transpose(A)` flips the first two dimensions of `A` without conjugating complex values. It is equivalent to the MATLAB syntax `A.'` and leaves higher dimensions untouched.

name: tril
summary: Lower triangular portion of a matrix or paged tensor.
description: `tril(A)` keeps the elements on and below a selected diagonal of `A` and sets everything above that diagonal to zero. The optional second argument `k` controls which diagonal is retained:

name: triu
summary: Upper triangular portion of a matrix or paged tensor.
description: `triu(A)` keeps the elements on and above a selected diagonal of `A` and sets everything below that diagonal to zero. The optional second argument `k` controls which diagonal is retained:

name: union
summary: Combine two arrays, returning their union with MATLAB-compatible ordering and index outputs.
description: `union(A, B)` creates the set-theoretic union of inputs `A` and `B`, returning a value array `C` that contains every distinct element (or row) appearing in either input.

name: unique
summary: Return the unique elements or rows of arrays with optional index outputs.
description: `unique` removes duplicates from its input while providing optional index outputs that map between the original data and the returned distinct values (or rows).

name: upper
summary: Convert strings, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors to uppercase.
description: `upper(text)` converts every alphabetic character in `text` to uppercase. It accepts string scalars, string arrays, character arrays, and cell arrays of character vectors, mirroring MATLAB behaviour.

name: var
summary: Variance of scalars, vectors, matrices, or N-D tensors with MATLAB-compatible options.
description: `var(x)` measures the spread of the elements in `x` by returning their variance.

name: vertcat
summary: Concatenate inputs vertically (dimension 1) just like MATLAB semicolons.
description: `vertcat(A1, A2, â¦)` vertically concatenates its inputs, matching the behavior of MATLAB's semicolon array construction `[A1; A2; â¦]`.

name: warning
summary: Display formatted warnings, control warning state, and query per-identifier settings.
description: `warning` emits diagnostic messages without aborting execution. It also provides a central interface for enabling, disabling, promoting, or querying warnings by identifier.

name: weboptions
summary: Create an options struct that configures webread and webwrite HTTP behaviour.
description: `weboptions` builds a MATLAB-style options struct that controls HTTP behaviour for functions such as `webread`, `webwrite`, and `websave`.

name: webread
summary: Download web content (JSON, text, or binary) over HTTP/HTTPS.
description: `webread` issues an HTTP or HTTPS request and returns the response body as a MATLAB-compatible value.

name: webwrite
summary: Send data to web services using HTTP POST/PUT requests and return the response.
description: `webwrite` sends data to an HTTP or HTTPS endpoint using methods such as `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, or `DELETE`.

name: which
summary: Identify which variable, builtin, script, class, or folder RunMat will execute for a given name.
description: `which name` reports exactly which entity RunMat will call when you invoke `name`. It follows MATLAB's search order:

name: who
summary: List the names of variables in the workspace or MAT-files (MATLAB-compatible).
description: `who` returns the names of variables that are visible in the active workspace.

name: whos
summary: List variables in the workspace or MAT-files with MATLAB-compatible metadata.
description: `whos` reports a MATLAB-style table describing each variable in the current workspace (or in a MAT-file when you pass `-file`).

name: write
summary: Write numeric or text data to a TCP/IP client.
description: `write(t, data)` transmits binary or textual data over the TCP/IP client returned by `tcpclient` (or `accept`).

name: writematrix
summary: Write numeric or string matrices to delimited text files with MATLAB-compatible defaults.
description: `writematrix(A, filename)` serialises numeric or string matrices to a text file using MATLAB-compatible defaults.

name: xor
summary: Element-wise logical XOR for scalars, arrays, and gpuArray values.
description: `xor(A, B)` returns the element-wise logical exclusive OR of its inputs. The result is `true` exactly when one, and only one, operand evaluates to non-zero (with `NaN` counting as non-zero).

name: zeros
summary: Create arrays filled with zeros.
description: `zeros` creates arrays filled with zeros. RunMat mirrors MATLAB semantics across the scalar, vector, matrix, and N-D forms, including `'like'` and `'logical'` options.
